Chaos erupted at Glasgow Airport as a car burst into flames, crashing into the terminal in what British Prime Minister Gordon Brown deemed a deliberate attack.
The incident, following thwarted car bomb plots in London, prompted heightened security measures across the UK.
Two suspects were arrested in connection with the attacks, signaling a potential link between the incidents.
The nation's threat level was raised to "critical," indicating an imminent threat.
Authorities urged vigilance and support from the public as they worked to ensure the safety of all British citizens.
